&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE COMPANY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;Tefron is a global B2B brand with a specialised focus in the activewear and intimates’ spaces. Our key values include innovating through garment design lead with solution based product and cutting-edge yarns. At the core of what we do we are focused on sustainability and doing good together as a community with innovation being the focal point of all our global projects. At Tefron, we are committed to promoting and celebrating diversity and inclusion within our team. No matter who you are, what you do or how you do it, we value unique talents, contributions and most importantly, respect.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Located in Midtown Manhattan, the intimates design team is a diverse team of creative and strategic thinkers who strive to innovate practical and fashionable product. This passionate team is detail-oriented, and solution focused. They are strong communicators who value and develop their cross functional relationships. This is a team of high performers who are constantly striving to develop personally and professionally, practicing open feedback in a trusting space. This team knows how to bring fun into their everyday, prioritising team connection &amp;amp; creative sessions together.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate Designer in the seamless space, you will play a vital role in the design and development of cutting-edge seamless apparel. Working closely with the design team, you will contribute to the creation of innovative, functional, and stylish garments that meets the needs of our target audience. This role involves translating concepts into tangible designs, collaborating with cross-functional teams, and staying updated on industry trends to ensure our products remain at the forefront of the market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU WILL:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiate product development packets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Update tech packs to reflect silo/construction changes throughout the product lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Loading items into CBX&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the conceptualization and development of seamless designs in collaboration with the design team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create detailed sketches, renderings, and digital illustrations to visualize design concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in creating seamless garment patterns, ensuring a balance between functionality, comfort, and aesthetics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage communication with overseas offices on product development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize and align needs with customer calendars to ensure on-time submissions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside cross-functional counter parts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support designers on preparing seasonal trend presentations based on understanding of product line and whitespace opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-3 years industry experience required; previous experience or internships in activewear or seamless design is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BA, BFA or BS in Design required (or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable in Adobe Suites platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding in 3D design, an asset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of garment construction, fabric properties, and production processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and collaboration skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE PERKS AND BENEFITS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
