&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;Tefron is a global B2B brand with a specialised focus in the activewear and intimates’ spaces. Our key values include innovating through garment design lead with solution based product and cutting-edge yarns. At the core of what we do we are focused on sustainability and doing good together as a community with innovation being the focal point of all our global projects. At Tefron, we are committed to promoting and celebrating diversity and inclusion within our team. No matter who you are, what you do or how you do it, we value unique talents, contributions and most importantly, respect.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Production team, the Production Coordinator will play a crucial role in ensuring the efficient operation of production processes. Your responsibilities will include various tasks such as purchase order (PO) creation, item creation, tech pack development, lab dip support, tracking the development critical path (DCP), assisting production managers, and managing time in action (TNA) for clients. Your role will contribute to the timely and quality production of garments while maintaining client satisfaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IN THIS ROLE, YOU WILL:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Purchase Order (PO) Creation:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize the ERP system to generate accurate and detailed purchase orders for raw materials, components, and supplies required for production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with supply chain teams to ensure timely and accurate order fulfillment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Item Creation:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain item records within the ERP system, ensuring accuracy and completeness of product information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with relevant departments to ensure that item specifications align with production requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tech Pack Creation:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop comprehensive technical packages (tech packs) that include detailed information on product specifications, materials, measurements, and construction methods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with design and product development teams to ensure tech packs align with design concepts and customer requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lab Dip Support:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate the lab dip process by working closely with the overseas team and customers to ensure color and quality standards are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively with external parties to resolve any issues related to lab dip approvals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Development Critical Path (DCP) Follow-Up:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and track the development critical path (DCP) to ensure that all milestones and deadlines are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to address any delays or issues that may impact the production timeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support for Project Managers and Customers:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist project managers and customers by providing necessary information, status updates, and support to ensure successful project execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with project stakeholders to address their concerns and needs effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
